
The #Y#Custom Menu#W# is a menu that you can create to suit your requiremens.
#G#
When available, the menu can be accessed from:
- Main Page menu.
- System Extensions Menu. A Hotkey can be assigned from System Hotkey Settings.

#Y#How:#W#
  1- Start the menu (from Main Page menu or from Extensions menu).
  2- The panel will ask to copy the sample files to your backup directory and will start the menu.
  3- Customize the file #Gn#ajpanel_menu.xml#W# to your needs (it includes description and many samples).

#Y#Main Features:#W#
- Recursive submenus can be added (unlimited recursion depth).
- You can customize your favourite AJPanel options into a submenu.
- You can direct a command, multiple commands and script files to the Terminal.
- The menu can be accessed from Main Page menu and from System Extensions Menu.
- A Hotkey can be assigned from System Hotkey Settings for easy access to the menu.
